parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Proximity to Accelerator Pedal
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The close proximity of the brake pedal to the accelerator pedal can cause unintended acceleration or braking, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The brake pedal is too close to the accelerator pedal
causing the driver's shoe to accidentally activate the brake while pressing the accelerator
making it difficult to operate the vehicle safely.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Feeling Soft or Spongy
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A soft or spongy brake pedal can cause the vehicle to take longer to stop, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
requiring more pressure to stop the vehicle
or the pedal travels further than usual before engaging the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure or lockup can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes fail to engage
or the vehicle continues to move after applying the brakes
or the brakes lock up
causing the vehicle to skid or lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to speed out of control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates rapidly or unexpectedly when the brake pedal is applied
making it difficult to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the airbag system can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on or off intermittently
or the airbag fails to deploy in a crash
or the wrong airbag deploys.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag Warning Light Illumination and Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag warning light can indicate a faulty airbag system, which can lead to failure to deploy in the event of an accident, potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates continuously
the airbag warning light comes on intermittently
the airbag warning light stays on for an extended period
the airbag warning light is accompanied by a faulty occupant weight sensor
the airbag warning light is accompanied by a faulty driver-side airbag.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty occupant weight sensor can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, and may lead to airbag failure to deploy in the event of an accident, potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates continuously
the airbag warning light comes on intermittently
the airbag warning light stays on for an extended period
the occupant weight sensor is faulty
the airbag warning light is accompanied by a faulty driver-side airbag.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of an accident can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates continuously
the airbag warning light comes on intermittently
the airbag warning light stays on for an extended period
the airbag fails to deploy in an accident
the airbag warning light is accompanied by a faulty driver-side airbag.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The coolant leakage can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage or failure, and the crash mode can cause the vehicle to shut off, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Coolant leakage
crash mode activation
safety alarm system check
vehicle shutting off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty door locks can cause the doors to lock up, trapping occupants inside, which can be life-threatening in emergency situations.
symptoms: Doors locking up
unable to unlock doors
faulty lock actuators
wiring harness issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle accelerating without pressing the gas pedal
vehicle shutting off when braking
RPM surging.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause loss of critical vehicle functions, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Gauges malfunctioning
no speedometer
no gas reading
no engine heat meter
message center malfunctioning
turn signals malfunctioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent electrical problems can cause loss of critical vehicle functions, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Dashboard
radio
climate controls turning off by themselves
wipers activating by themselves
SRS warnings displayed
fuel door button not activating
ignition not activating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear tail light assembly failure can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Intermittent rear tail light assembly
no rear tail lights at night
faulty CEM.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump electronic module can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of propulsion and increasing the risk of a collision or serious physical injury.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the check engine warning light illuminates
the vehicle veers to the right
the vehicle will not restart
the fuel pump module needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Insufficient Sealing of Fuel Pump Electronic Module
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Insufficient sealing of the fuel pump electronic module can lead to water ingress corrosion, causing the unit to fail, resulting in increased, decreased, or loss of fuel pressure, and engine stalling.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loss of fuel pressure
corrosion of the fuel pump electronic module.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various malfunctions, including windshield wipers, power windows and doors, gas gauge, and airbag light issues, which can lead to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: Windshield wipers suddenly cut on and off
power windows and doors do not work
gas gauge always shows no fuel
airbag light comes on
trunk does not open.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected lock-up or failure of the steering system can cause loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult or impossible to turn
the steering wheel locks up
the vehicle is hard to steer
the steering wheel freezes
and error messages may appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electrical system can cause a range of problems, including loss of vehicle control, unexpected acceleration, and failure of critical safety systems, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The dashboard displays malfunction
panels fade in and out
speedometer
radio
and temperature gauge become unreadable
the vehicle accelerates on its own
and error messages may appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bag system can increase the risk of injuries and fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The air bag light illuminates
and the air bag system may not deploy properly in the event of an accident.
